PART 6: FORBIDDEN H — PATTERN ACROSS n
======================================================================

n=3: Forbidden H = {}
n=4: Forbidden H = {}
n=5: Forbidden H = {7}
n=6: Forbidden H = {7, 21, 35, 39}

7 = 1 + 2·3: α₁=3 impossible
21 = 1 + 2·10: α₁=10 impossible at n=5; at n=6 α₁=10 IS possible (with α₂=2)
     But 21 requires (α₁, α₂) = (10, 0) which doesn't occur, OR
     (α₁, α₂) with 1+2α₁+4α₂=21 → 2α₁+4α₂=20 → α₁+2α₂=10
     Possible: (10,0), (8,1), (6,2), (4,3), (2,4), (0,5)

